1
00:00:01,877 --> 00:00:04,421
Do you have what it
takes to Buddyfight?

2
00:00:04,421 --> 00:00:07,049
Choose your favorite world
and use special cards

3
00:00:07,049 --> 00:00:10,344
to summon its powerful
monsters into reality.

4
00:00:10,344 --> 00:00:12,554
Challenge other
fighters and Buddy Call

5
00:00:12,554 --> 00:00:15,474
your toughest ally
to fight by your side.

6
00:00:15,474 --> 00:00:18,227
Get ready to raise the flag!

7
00:00:18,227 --> 00:00:20,312
Counter final!

8
00:00:20,312 --> 00:00:22,189
I cast!

9
00:00:22,189 --> 00:00:28,612
♪

10
00:00:28,612 --> 00:00:30,656
Let the world distort.

11
00:00:30,656 --> 00:00:32,407
♪

12
00:00:32,407 --> 00:00:36,703
Turn back the sands of time and
erase all sadness from the past.

13
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:39,164
Sword of Nothingness,

14
00:00:39,164 --> 00:00:41,708
Distortion...

15
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:44,836
Punisher!

16
00:00:44,836 --> 00:00:48,215
(rumbling)

17
00:00:48,215 --> 00:02:23,393
♪

18
00:02:28,774 --> 00:02:31,943
The live coverage of the
Gaen Cup has resumed, sir.

19
00:02:31,943 --> 00:02:33,945
Put it on the main screen.

20
00:02:33,945 --> 00:02:36,114
You must believe how
shocked I am to discover

21
00:02:36,114 --> 00:02:38,450
his true identity,
we couldn't have known

22
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:41,953
that the Purgatory Knight
was Tasuku Ryuenji.

23
00:02:41,953 --> 00:02:45,082
Yes, yes, of course, we would
never have hidden the truth.

24
00:02:45,082 --> 00:02:47,334
I can only speculate
why he wished to hide

25
00:02:47,334 --> 00:02:49,086
his identity from all of us.

26
00:02:49,086 --> 00:02:51,338
Perhaps for some reason
he wanted to compete

27
00:02:51,338 --> 00:02:53,799
in my tournament as an unknown.

28
00:02:53,799 --> 00:02:55,342
But did you see it?

29
00:02:55,342 --> 00:02:57,427
That counter final card he used.

30
00:02:57,427 --> 00:02:59,721
It's a perfect example
of the new cards

31
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:01,056
that will soon be available

32
00:03:01,056 --> 00:03:03,767
as the world's most
incredible game

33
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:04,224
continues to improve and evolve.

34
00:03:04,224 --> 00:03:09,145
(clapping)

35
00:03:09,145 --> 00:03:12,398
(applause)

36
00:03:12,398 --> 00:03:16,110
(cheering)

37
00:03:23,326 --> 00:03:25,411
I was afraid that
this might happen.

38
00:03:25,411 --> 00:03:28,623
Still, it's hard to believe
he'd take such drastic measures.

39
00:03:28,623 --> 00:03:32,293
It seems Team Purgatory
is actually Team Disaster,

40
00:03:32,293 --> 00:03:33,628
meaning that Tasuku‐‐

41
00:03:33,628 --> 00:03:35,672
Has become a member of Disaster?

42
00:03:35,672 --> 00:03:39,592
‐You really think so?
‐It is possible.

43
00:03:39,592 --> 00:03:41,427
Well, well, what
do we have here?

44
00:03:41,427 --> 00:03:44,264
Looks like you're wasting
valuable work time gossiping.

45
00:03:44,264 --> 00:03:47,433
‐No, Commander, we were just‐‐
‐Uh‐uh‐uh.

46
00:03:47,433 --> 00:03:50,228
Back to work, you two.

47
00:03:50,228 --> 00:03:52,397
We were discussing
Tasuku Ryuenji.

48
00:03:52,397 --> 00:03:54,566
I see, who would've
guessed he'd enter

49
00:03:54,566 --> 00:03:56,818
the Gaen Cup under
an assumed name?

50
00:03:56,818 --> 00:03:59,612
The scandal, this means
he has no intention

51
00:03:59,612 --> 00:04:01,823
of returning to us.

52
00:04:01,823 --> 00:04:04,450
I guess it's probably
for the best.

53
00:04:04,450 --> 00:04:06,703
I'm glad we cut him
loose when we did.

54
00:04:06,703 --> 00:04:09,330
(laughing and groaning)

55
00:04:09,330 --> 00:04:13,459
♪

56
00:04:13,459 --> 00:04:16,462
There can be no doubt,
Kyoya Gaen is the one

57
00:04:16,462 --> 00:04:18,590
behind Nobari and his cronies.

58
00:04:18,590 --> 00:04:20,675
We now know the
face of our enemy.

59
00:04:20,675 --> 00:04:24,095
I agree, time for phase two.

60
00:04:24,095 --> 00:04:25,638
Hm.

61
00:04:25,638 --> 00:04:28,016
(panting)

62
00:04:28,016 --> 00:04:31,561
Wait, you're really
gonna talk to Tasuku?

63
00:04:31,561 --> 00:04:33,688
I have got to get
to the bottom of this.

64
00:04:33,688 --> 00:04:35,565
I gotta know what he's thinking.

65
00:04:35,565 --> 00:04:37,942
Welcome back to the
Gaen Cup semifinal

66
00:04:37,942 --> 00:04:40,194
between Team Destiny
and Team Purgatory.

67
00:04:40,194 --> 00:04:41,404
And if you haven't heard,

68
00:04:41,404 --> 00:04:43,865
we had a surprising
appearance by Tasuku Ryuenji.

69
00:04:43,865 --> 00:04:47,577
Even with his frosty cool new
look he's still super dreamy.

70
00:04:47,577 --> 00:04:51,080
Now get ready, 'cause the second
fight of the match will feature

71
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:55,543
Team Purgatory's Rouga Aragami
and his Buddy, Cerberus Ace.

72
00:04:55,543 --> 00:04:58,671
Opposing him from Team
Destiny is Jin Magatsu

73
00:04:58,671 --> 00:05:01,883
and his Buddy, Evil
in Heart, Yamigitsune.

74
00:05:01,883 --> 00:05:04,552
It's a rare
canine‐monster showdown.

75
00:05:04,552 --> 00:05:06,304
Ruff‐ruff‐ro!

76
00:05:06,304 --> 00:05:09,057
It's true, they're both
canines, but a little fox

77
00:05:09,057 --> 00:05:11,476
is no match for
a ferocious wolf.

78
00:05:11,476 --> 00:05:12,727
You're all talk.

79
00:05:12,727 --> 00:05:16,189
My fox here will have
you running in circles.

80
00:05:16,189 --> 00:05:19,108
I've wanted to fight you,
Magatsu, since I was at Aibo.

81
00:05:19,108 --> 00:05:21,903
I just hope that your
nickname, The Uncrowned King,

82
00:05:21,903 --> 00:05:24,155
doesn't prove a
disappointment to me.

83
00:05:24,155 --> 00:05:27,241
I guess I should be flattered,
but guys like you are why

84
00:05:27,241 --> 00:05:29,577
I avoided events like
this in the first place.

85
00:05:29,577 --> 00:05:31,996
By agreeing to have
Buddyfights with show‐offs,

86
00:05:31,996 --> 00:05:34,749
‐I risk damaging my reputation.
‐What do you mean?

87
00:05:34,749 --> 00:05:38,544
I mean, if I was foolish enough
to beat you, I'd lose my title.

88
00:05:38,544 --> 00:05:42,006
Are you suggesting that you
could beat me if you wanted to?

89
00:05:42,006 --> 00:05:45,760
What if I am, there's only one
way to find out, isn't there?

90
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:47,929
♪

91
00:05:47,929 --> 00:05:51,057
(laughing)

92
00:05:51,057 --> 00:05:53,434
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, what's going on?

93
00:05:53,434 --> 00:05:55,979
Did I just hear those
two laughing together?

94
00:05:55,979 --> 00:05:58,940
Are they forming some sort of
bond no one will understand?

95
00:05:58,940 --> 00:06:02,276
Kind of like my
bond with Tasuku.

96
00:06:02,276 --> 00:06:04,612
The power of the Ace
will destroy you!

97
00:06:04,612 --> 00:06:07,198
Dark Luminize,

98
00:06:07,198 --> 00:06:10,493
Ace Defeat!

99
00:06:10,493 --> 00:06:13,913
A terrifying spectacle's
about to begin.

100
00:06:13,913 --> 00:06:16,499
Luminize,

101
00:06:16,499 --> 00:06:19,627
Crazy Phantom Carnival.

102
00:06:19,627 --> 00:06:21,713
Buddy...

103
00:06:21,713 --> 00:06:22,964
fight!

104
00:06:22,964 --> 00:06:24,966
‐Time to raise the flag.
‐Time to raise the flag.

105
00:06:24,966 --> 00:06:27,385
I'm with Danger World.

106
00:06:27,385 --> 00:06:31,055
I fight for Katana World.

107
00:06:31,055 --> 00:06:33,975
Tasuku, open up!

108
00:06:33,975 --> 00:06:35,643
What can I do for you?

109
00:06:35,643 --> 00:06:38,813
You are aware this is not
your team's waiting room.

110
00:06:38,813 --> 00:06:43,484
Drop the act, Ice Queen, we
have business with Tasuku.

111
00:06:46,029 --> 00:06:48,448
Gleipnir.

112
00:06:48,448 --> 00:06:50,825
‐Ahh!
‐Stop it!

113
00:06:50,825 --> 00:06:53,244
Disaster Force has the
ability to make the power

114
00:06:53,244 --> 00:06:56,164
of the cards into reality.

115
00:06:56,164 --> 00:06:58,499
You're tempted
by it, aren't you?

116
00:06:58,499 --> 00:07:02,295
You won't brainwash me like
you did all the others.

117
00:07:02,295 --> 00:07:03,880
Oh, really?

118
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:06,174
Like you did with
Kiri and Shosetsu,

119
00:07:06,174 --> 00:07:08,593
and then you used your
power to manipulate Tasuku

120
00:07:08,593 --> 00:07:09,969
when he was feeling low.

121
00:07:09,969 --> 00:07:12,263
For some reason, everyone
loses it when they get

122
00:07:12,263 --> 00:07:14,557
that Dark Core Deck
Case in their hands.

123
00:07:14,557 --> 00:07:16,684
You Disaster guys keep
saying that you're trying

124
00:07:16,684 --> 00:07:18,519
to save the world,
but how do you think

125
00:07:18,519 --> 00:07:20,772
hurting people is
gonna do that, huh?

126
00:07:20,772 --> 00:07:24,025
‐You're a joke!
‐Sofia.

127
00:07:24,025 --> 00:07:26,778
Please free Drum
from those chains.

128
00:07:26,778 --> 00:07:28,780
You are here.

129
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:31,157
Ahhh, that hurt!

130
00:07:31,157 --> 00:07:35,077
Let's go, you can't stay
here with these guys.

131
00:07:35,077 --> 00:07:38,539
Actually, Gao, you're
the one who should leave.

132
00:07:38,539 --> 00:07:41,876
Understand I'm not being
manipulated by anyone here.

133
00:07:41,876 --> 00:07:43,503
I chose Disaster.

134
00:07:43,503 --> 00:07:46,881
I joined of my own free will.

135
00:07:46,881 --> 00:07:49,383
‐That's not true!
‐It is true.

136
00:07:49,383 --> 00:07:52,678
I lost a Buddyfight to Kyoya
and it opened my eyes.

137
00:07:52,678 --> 00:07:57,183
‐You wouldn't get it.
‐Tasuku!

138
00:07:57,183 --> 00:07:59,227
Rouga has the first move.

139
00:07:59,227 --> 00:08:00,978
Charge and Draw.

140
00:08:00,978 --> 00:08:03,856
Vanquish all with
everlasting strength.

141
00:08:03,856 --> 00:08:08,653
I equip Explosive Axe,
Ricdeau Demon Slay!

142
00:08:08,653 --> 00:08:11,072
I caught your fight
against Shosetsu.

143
00:08:11,072 --> 00:08:14,784
I know the restrictions tied
to equipping that item.

144
00:08:14,784 --> 00:08:18,579
You can't call a monster
to your center position.

145
00:08:18,579 --> 00:08:21,249
Gotta say, it takes guts
to leave yourself open.

146
00:08:21,249 --> 00:08:22,917
I'd never do that.

147
00:08:22,917 --> 00:08:24,669
So you're not a
big risk taker, huh?

148
00:08:24,669 --> 00:08:26,128
Well, I'll show you
what it really means

149
00:08:26,128 --> 00:08:27,588
to live on the edge.

150
00:08:27,588 --> 00:08:30,550
I cast set spell,
Final Battle Skill,

151
00:08:30,550 --> 00:08:32,510
MAJI Demon Slay.

152
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:35,972
♪

153
00:08:35,972 --> 00:08:38,224
He just blocked
your center area.

154
00:08:38,224 --> 00:08:40,101
This'll be fun.

155
00:08:40,101 --> 00:08:41,936
That wiped the smile
off your face.

156
00:08:41,936 --> 00:08:44,438
As long as this set spell's
engaged, we will not be able

157
00:08:44,438 --> 00:08:48,484
to call size two monsters
or smaller to the center.

158
00:08:48,484 --> 00:08:50,778
Brace yourself, here he comes!

159
00:08:50,778 --> 00:08:53,614
(shouting)

160
00:08:53,614 --> 00:08:56,075
♪

161
00:08:56,075 --> 00:08:59,453
End of move.

162
00:08:59,453 --> 00:09:01,622
That's a new one,
this set spell forces

163
00:09:01,622 --> 00:09:04,250
both players to leave
their center wide open.

164
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:06,878
I guess now Jin has no
choice but to match Rouga's

165
00:09:06,878 --> 00:09:09,589
no nonsense fighting style.

166
00:09:09,589 --> 00:09:12,800
Poor Jin, his Skull Warrior deck
is just not built for that.

167
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:16,220
It was crafted to slowly
cause damage to his opponents

168
00:09:16,220 --> 00:09:19,140
with monsters than can return
after being destroyed.

169
00:09:19,140 --> 00:09:21,058
Show's over, yo,
sounds like Jin‐Boy's

170
00:09:21,058 --> 00:09:22,810
on the express train outta here.

171
00:09:22,810 --> 00:09:25,938
What do you think there, Zanya?

172
00:09:35,615 --> 00:09:37,241
And draw.

173
00:09:37,241 --> 00:09:40,328
Charge and Draw.

174
00:09:40,328 --> 00:09:42,872
You think you've got
me at a disadvantage.

175
00:09:42,872 --> 00:09:44,373
I know something you don't.

176
00:09:44,373 --> 00:09:46,167
Now sit back and watch.

177
00:09:46,167 --> 00:09:49,545
I call Tempest, Garo‐oh
to the right position.

178
00:09:49,545 --> 00:09:53,841
And to the left,
Treachery, Jakikarasu.

179
00:09:53,841 --> 00:09:56,052
I activate Garo‐oh's ability.

180
00:09:56,052 --> 00:09:58,095
By paying one gauge, his power

181
00:09:58,095 --> 00:10:01,182
increases by 3,000.

182
00:10:01,182 --> 00:10:04,185
He also gets the ability
to do a double attack.

183
00:10:04,185 --> 00:10:06,270
No pun intended, but
I'm more than equipped

184
00:10:06,270 --> 00:10:08,689
to punish you with
some frontal attacks.

185
00:10:08,689 --> 00:10:12,068
Now, Garo‐oh, go say
hello to the fighter.

186
00:10:12,068 --> 00:10:15,029
(shouting)

187
00:10:15,029 --> 00:10:18,074
Garo Slash!

188
00:10:18,074 --> 00:10:21,118
One more time!

189
00:10:21,118 --> 00:10:23,913
Feel the burn!

190
00:10:23,913 --> 00:10:28,084
Treachery, Jakikarasu, why not
play him your favorite tune?

191
00:10:28,084 --> 00:10:31,212
♪

192
00:10:31,212 --> 00:10:34,048
‐White Noise!
‐End of move.

193
00:10:34,048 --> 00:10:38,052
How is Rouga still standing
after that triple attack?

194
00:10:38,052 --> 00:10:42,014
Look at that smile, he actually
seems to be enjoying this.

195
00:10:42,014 --> 00:10:44,892
As Garo‐oh can only stay
on the field for one turn,

196
00:10:44,892 --> 00:10:47,728
he's now eliminated.

197
00:10:47,728 --> 00:10:49,605
Oh well, what can you do?

198
00:10:49,605 --> 00:10:51,857
Your move.

199
00:10:51,857 --> 00:10:54,277
I thought you'd at least
have the courage to equip

200
00:10:54,277 --> 00:10:57,238
an item and attack me directly.

201
00:10:57,238 --> 00:10:59,615
And put all my cards
on the table?

202
00:10:59,615 --> 00:11:02,535
Your wit will be your downfall.

203
00:11:02,535 --> 00:11:06,998
I Buddy Call Armorknight,
Cerberus Ace to the right.

204
00:11:06,998 --> 00:11:09,875
Rouga gains one life
point with a Buddy Gift.

205
00:11:09,875 --> 00:11:11,627
Sic him, Ace.

206
00:11:11,627 --> 00:11:14,714
(whooshing noise)

207
00:11:14,714 --> 00:11:17,216
♪

208
00:11:17,216 --> 00:11:19,760
Demonic equip combination.

209
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:21,804
Cerberus Ace
has entered the soul

210
00:11:21,804 --> 00:11:24,849
of Explosive Axe,
Ricdeau Demon Slay.

211
00:11:24,849 --> 00:11:26,559
He put Ace into the card's soul

212
00:11:26,559 --> 00:11:28,936
and increased the
item's critical by two.

213
00:11:28,936 --> 00:11:31,689
I call Armorknight
Minotaur to the right,

214
00:11:31,689 --> 00:11:35,109
and Armorknight Ogre
to the left.

215
00:11:35,109 --> 00:11:37,111
Rouga shows he means
business setting up

216
00:11:37,111 --> 00:11:39,280
his triple threat
fighting formation.

217
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:43,534
Copy cat, it's just
like the Gao formation.

218
00:11:43,534 --> 00:11:47,955
So then, Minotaur has a critical
of three, and Ogre's is two.

219
00:11:47,955 --> 00:11:51,167
Explosive Axe, Ricdeau Demon
Slay normally has a critical

220
00:11:51,167 --> 00:11:53,502
of three, but in this case,

221
00:11:53,502 --> 00:11:56,630
with Ace in its soul
it gets increased to five.

222
00:11:56,630 --> 00:11:59,884
That's a total critical
of ten and one attack.

223
00:11:59,884 --> 00:12:03,304
It's just like Rouga to set
up such an awesome move.

224
00:12:03,304 --> 00:12:06,682
He can't lose this now.

225
00:12:06,682 --> 00:12:08,559
Say your goodbyes, Your Majesty.

226
00:12:08,559 --> 00:12:11,020
No one can defend
against ten critical.

227
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:12,396
Hold on just a minute.

228
00:12:12,396 --> 00:12:14,815
Even if I can't call a
monster to the center,

229
00:12:14,815 --> 00:12:19,779
I can still move Jakikarasu
over to protect me instead.

230
00:12:19,779 --> 00:12:21,197
Don't waste my time!

231
00:12:21,197 --> 00:12:23,532
Ogre, clear that pretender
out of the center.

232
00:12:23,532 --> 00:12:25,826
Ogre!

233
00:12:25,826 --> 00:12:28,162
(explosive noises)

234
00:12:28,162 --> 00:12:30,247
That was easy, now I cast

235
00:12:30,247 --> 00:12:32,833
Demon Way, Geppakugiri.

236
00:12:32,833 --> 00:12:35,628
He did it, when an opponent
defeats one of your monsters

237
00:12:35,628 --> 00:12:38,339
the effect of that counter
spell takes out one of theirs

238
00:12:38,339 --> 00:12:40,674
at the same time, way to go.

239
00:12:40,674 --> 00:12:43,844
I always say, they aren't
destroyed for nothing.

240
00:12:43,844 --> 00:12:45,679
Looks like you're wide open.

241
00:12:45,679 --> 00:12:49,517
There's nothing standing
between us to protect you now.

242
00:12:49,517 --> 00:12:51,852
Ricdeau Demon Slay!

243
00:12:51,852 --> 00:12:53,771
I cast.

244
00:12:53,771 --> 00:12:56,190
‐Huh?
‐Art of Body Replacement.

245
00:12:56,190 --> 00:12:58,359
No matter how powerful
your attack is,

246
00:12:58,359 --> 00:13:00,778
it's useless if it doesn't
hit your opponent.

247
00:13:00,778 --> 00:13:02,571
I don't believe what I'm seeing!

248
00:13:02,571 --> 00:13:04,073
Jin's Art of Body Replacement

249
00:13:04,073 --> 00:13:06,367
completely nullifies
his opponent's attack!

250
00:13:06,367 --> 00:13:08,536
Who would've guessed that
he could survive an attack

251
00:13:08,536 --> 00:13:11,997
of 10 damage without
even a single scratch!

252
00:13:11,997 --> 00:13:13,874
Not bad, kid.

253
00:13:13,874 --> 00:13:16,168
Good to see you finally
giving everything you've got

254
00:13:16,168 --> 00:13:18,379
to win a fight, but why now?

255
00:13:18,379 --> 00:13:21,257
What made you decide to
start taking it seriously?

256
00:13:21,257 --> 00:13:22,883
I realized I was wrong.

257
00:13:22,883 --> 00:13:26,387
To be honest, you could even say
that I finally saw the light.

258
00:13:26,387 --> 00:13:27,930
What're you talking about?

259
00:13:27,930 --> 00:13:30,266
Like you, I fell into
a world of darkness.

260
00:13:30,266 --> 00:13:33,227
For the longest time, I didn't
think I could trust people.

261
00:13:33,227 --> 00:13:36,605
Sadly, the only thing I found
I could believe in was money.

262
00:13:36,605 --> 00:13:39,817
For you, that thing
has always been power.

263
00:13:39,817 --> 00:13:41,944
You crave it, so much in fact,

264
00:13:41,944 --> 00:13:44,780
that you've descended
into darkness for it.

265
00:13:44,780 --> 00:13:47,324
You don't know me.

266
00:13:47,324 --> 00:13:50,578
I know you're like anyone
else living in darkness.

267
00:13:50,578 --> 00:13:52,955
You long to see the
sun again, like I did.

268
00:13:52,955 --> 00:13:56,083
That's what inspired
me to try harder.

269
00:13:56,083 --> 00:13:59,628
‐That sun is Mikado?
‐Don't make me say it,

270
00:13:59,628 --> 00:14:02,381
it's embarrassing,
but you're right.

271
00:14:02,381 --> 00:14:05,426
He's the one who helped me
rise out of the darkness.

272
00:14:05,426 --> 00:14:08,929
You're saying that for you,
the sun is your friend?

273
00:14:08,929 --> 00:14:12,141
‐Then it'll be the same for me.
‐Huh?

274
00:14:12,141 --> 00:14:14,560
♪

275
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:18,439
In honor of my friend,
I, Rouga Aragami

276
00:14:18,439 --> 00:14:22,234
promise you this, I will
not lose this battle.

277
00:14:22,234 --> 00:14:26,405
I told you about the day that
I decided to protect people,

278
00:14:26,405 --> 00:14:29,992
when I thought it was
the duty bestowed upon me.

279
00:14:29,992 --> 00:14:32,953
And then the Future Force
awakened within me.

280
00:14:32,953 --> 00:14:36,582
But it‐‐I didn't know that
it would never be enough.

281
00:14:36,582 --> 00:14:38,876
♪

282
00:14:38,876 --> 00:14:43,672
Game over, winner, Kyoya Gaen.

283
00:14:43,672 --> 00:14:45,299
I just lost.

284
00:14:45,299 --> 00:14:48,219
I can't believe
Kyoya defeated me.

285
00:14:48,219 --> 00:14:50,804
You say that the Disaster
Force and the Future Force

286
00:14:50,804 --> 00:14:53,307
are the same thing,
but I just won.

287
00:14:53,307 --> 00:14:56,852
So tell me, can you tell
the difference between them?

288
00:14:56,852 --> 00:15:00,064
♪

289
00:15:00,064 --> 00:15:01,482
You're in a rush to grow up

290
00:15:01,482 --> 00:15:03,484
because you want
to protect people.

291
00:15:03,484 --> 00:15:06,654
Take it from me,
you're way off base.

292
00:15:06,654 --> 00:15:08,948
You're chasing
after an illusion.

293
00:15:08,948 --> 00:15:10,366
What do you mean?

294
00:15:10,366 --> 00:15:13,535
A lot of adults these days
only think about themselves.

295
00:15:13,535 --> 00:15:15,496
You know it as well as I do.

296
00:15:15,496 --> 00:15:17,498
Just look at the
criminal fighters who use

297
00:15:17,498 --> 00:15:19,750
their Buddy's powers
to commit crimes.

298
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:22,211
Or the high‐ranking members
of the Buddy Police

299
00:15:22,211 --> 00:15:24,838
who swore to maintain
law and protect us,

300
00:15:24,838 --> 00:15:27,258
but have now become corrupted.

301
00:15:27,258 --> 00:15:30,386
Do you really think that you can
achieve any sense of justice

302
00:15:30,386 --> 00:15:32,972
by joining forces with them?

303
00:15:32,972 --> 00:15:35,391
In the end, you're
not being protected.

304
00:15:35,391 --> 00:15:38,936
All they're doing is using you.

305
00:15:38,936 --> 00:15:41,188
Are you saying that
I've been nothing

306
00:15:41,188 --> 00:15:44,900
but a pawn this whole time?

307
00:15:44,900 --> 00:15:48,404
Trust me, the society that
we live in today won't last,

308
00:15:48,404 --> 00:15:51,824
but the new generation
can change the future.

309
00:15:51,824 --> 00:15:55,369
So please, join me.

310
00:15:55,369 --> 00:15:59,623
We both know that
this is what you need.

311
00:15:59,623 --> 00:16:02,668
Use this Dark Core to
show those crooked adults

312
00:16:02,668 --> 00:16:04,795
your sense of justice.

313
00:16:04,795 --> 00:16:06,714
We can be friends if you accept,

314
00:16:06,714 --> 00:16:09,758
and together we'll
save the world.

315
00:16:09,758 --> 00:16:11,635
Together?

316
00:16:11,635 --> 00:16:13,721
To save the world.

317
00:16:13,721 --> 00:16:19,268
♪

318
00:16:19,268 --> 00:16:21,603
That's why you left
the Buddy Police?

319
00:16:21,603 --> 00:16:24,273
You think that joining
Disaster is the answer?

320
00:16:24,273 --> 00:16:26,400
And tell me, just what
are you planning to do

321
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,736
with that Dark Core
Deck Case anyway?

322
00:16:28,736 --> 00:16:30,946
He'll use it to
increase our numbers

323
00:16:30,946 --> 00:16:33,240
and help recreate the world.

324
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:34,908
That's enough talk for now.

325
00:16:34,908 --> 00:16:36,744
You have a decision to make.

326
00:16:36,744 --> 00:16:39,413
Will you accept this
Dark Core or won't you?

327
00:16:39,413 --> 00:16:43,208
‐Tell me now.
‐I don't know, I...

328
00:16:45,252 --> 00:16:48,756
Stay true to yourself,
Gao, it's who you are.

329
00:16:48,756 --> 00:16:51,425
Yeah.

330
00:16:55,054 --> 00:16:57,431
We have no choice but
to respect your decision,

331
00:16:57,431 --> 00:16:59,600
but first, I'll need
to erase your memory

332
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,436
‐of this conversation.
‐No, don't!

333
00:17:02,436 --> 00:17:05,022
‐Dragonic Shoot!
‐Nice try.

334
00:17:05,022 --> 00:17:08,233
Breathen Gard!

335
00:17:08,233 --> 00:17:10,277
‐Leave him alone!
‐Grim Reaper.

336
00:17:10,277 --> 00:17:12,905
‐Kiri?
‐Is that the Disaster Force?

337
00:17:12,905 --> 00:17:15,991
Not quite, but be
prepared for anything.

338
00:17:15,991 --> 00:17:19,119
‐Why do this?
‐Jackknife Dragon!

339
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:22,122
(flames whooshing)

340
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:25,834
It's Jack!

341
00:17:25,834 --> 00:17:28,253
Kiri, do you wanna tell
us what's going on?

342
00:17:28,253 --> 00:17:30,422
I can't really explain it.

343
00:17:30,422 --> 00:17:32,466
Even though I gave
up the Dark Core,

344
00:17:32,466 --> 00:17:35,427
I can still make the
power of the cards real.

345
00:17:35,427 --> 00:17:38,639
Now listen, Tasuku, I know it
won't mean much coming from me,

346
00:17:38,639 --> 00:17:40,557
but Jack has something
he needs to say to you.

347
00:17:40,557 --> 00:17:43,477
Don't bother, I know what
he's gonna say already.

348
00:17:43,477 --> 00:17:45,479
Please don't.

349
00:17:45,479 --> 00:17:49,024
Tasuku, you said a bond
like ours was unbreakable.

350
00:17:49,024 --> 00:17:50,776
♪

351
00:17:50,776 --> 00:17:54,988
It is, you'll always be the most
important thing in my life.

352
00:17:54,988 --> 00:17:56,990
Then why'd you go off
and become Buddies

353
00:17:56,990 --> 00:17:59,326
with that wack‐job
Demios Sword guy?

354
00:17:59,326 --> 00:18:01,662
Is that how you treat
people in your family?

355
00:18:01,662 --> 00:18:04,915
I guess us dragons have a
different sense of loyalty.

356
00:18:04,915 --> 00:18:06,667
Hm.

357
00:18:06,667 --> 00:18:09,420
It's not true, not at all.

358
00:18:09,420 --> 00:18:11,672
Life's great when I'm with you.

359
00:18:11,672 --> 00:18:14,633
You make me feel like I belong,
but that's not a luxury

360
00:18:14,633 --> 00:18:17,720
I can afford, not if
I want to do my duty.

361
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:20,013
I'm the one who has
to protect people.

362
00:18:20,013 --> 00:18:22,766
So in order to bring
happiness to others,

363
00:18:22,766 --> 00:18:26,228
I have to put aside
my own happiness.

364
00:18:26,228 --> 00:18:28,522
That Dark Core is
rotting your brain!

365
00:18:28,522 --> 00:18:32,025
The truth is, as long
as I'm protected by you,

366
00:18:32,025 --> 00:18:33,986
I can't become stronger.

367
00:18:33,986 --> 00:18:35,571
I hope you understand.

368
00:18:35,571 --> 00:18:37,406
Even though you're
my best friend,

369
00:18:37,406 --> 00:18:39,283
you're my greatest weakness.

370
00:18:39,283 --> 00:18:42,661
What're you saying?

371
00:18:42,661 --> 00:18:44,997
This is the new card that
I've picked out for you.

372
00:18:44,997 --> 00:18:48,834
‐What do you think?
‐Demios Sword Dragon.

373
00:18:48,834 --> 00:18:52,045
He's unique in that he can gain
strength simply by destroying

374
00:18:52,045 --> 00:18:54,298
one of his comrades
in the field.

375
00:18:54,298 --> 00:18:57,217
Gaining strength by
destroying an ally.

376
00:18:57,217 --> 00:19:00,387
‐I've done it before.
‐No, wait!

377
00:19:00,387 --> 00:19:03,432
If you use that card,
you know what'll happen!

378
00:19:03,432 --> 00:19:06,602
I'm sorry, forgive me.

379
00:19:06,602 --> 00:19:08,645
Tasuku!

380
00:19:08,645 --> 00:19:11,607
♪

381
00:19:11,607 --> 00:19:14,067
A human and a dragon unite!

382
00:19:14,067 --> 00:19:17,404
Behold Jackknife Gold Ritter!

383
00:19:17,404 --> 00:19:19,698
If I must,

384
00:19:19,698 --> 00:19:22,785
I'll discard the one
thing I cherish most.

385
00:19:22,785 --> 00:19:24,870
I know now it's the only way.

386
00:19:24,870 --> 00:19:27,539
Congratulations,
that wasn't so hard,

387
00:19:27,539 --> 00:19:31,460
and as your reward,
you get to be my friend.

388
00:19:31,460 --> 00:19:32,920
No thanks.

389
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:35,923
I don't want any
friends or family.

390
00:19:35,923 --> 00:19:38,467
I wanna be all on my own.

391
00:19:38,467 --> 00:19:42,513
I've made up my mind,
not get outta here or else!

392
00:19:42,513 --> 00:19:45,641
(explosions)

393
00:19:45,641 --> 00:19:47,684
Ragnarok!

394
00:19:47,684 --> 00:19:51,396
(wind howling)

395
00:19:58,487 --> 00:20:00,280
Gao, get up.

396
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:02,616
Huh?

397
00:20:02,616 --> 00:20:04,701
Hope you had a nice
nap there, kid,

398
00:20:04,701 --> 00:20:07,079
'cause we got a
lot of work to do.

399
00:20:07,079 --> 00:20:10,374
Drum's right, I'll tell
you what I just told him.

400
00:20:10,374 --> 00:20:13,043
There's a reason that Noboru,
Jin, and Kazane teamed up

401
00:20:13,043 --> 00:20:15,254
for this Gaen Cup tournament.

402
00:20:15,254 --> 00:20:17,506
They're working together
to reveal the full extent

403
00:20:17,506 --> 00:20:19,842
of Disaster's powers
and influence,

404
00:20:19,842 --> 00:20:23,178
and to learn as much as they
can about Disaster's plans.

405
00:20:23,178 --> 00:20:24,972
♪

406
00:20:24,972 --> 00:20:27,766
I suppose you could say
that they're undercover.

407
00:20:27,766 --> 00:20:29,601
But why are they doing it?

408
00:20:29,601 --> 00:20:32,896
‐It's all for you.
‐You sure about that?

409
00:20:32,896 --> 00:20:35,274
You've only got two cards
left in your hand,

410
00:20:35,274 --> 00:20:37,401
but I know there's an
ace up your sleeve.

411
00:20:37,401 --> 00:20:38,986
So let's see it already.

412
00:20:38,986 --> 00:20:42,030
I cast Lord Aura Meditation.

413
00:20:42,030 --> 00:20:43,907
Final phase.

414
00:20:43,907 --> 00:20:46,743
He increased his gauge so
that he could use his impact.

415
00:20:46,743 --> 00:20:51,331
I change Demon Slay's vow into
a blade and release it now!

416
00:20:51,331 --> 00:20:55,127
I cast Ultimate Battle Skill.

417
00:20:55,127 --> 00:20:58,714
Mega Demon Slay!

418
00:20:58,714 --> 00:21:01,466
(screaming)

419
00:21:01,466 --> 00:21:03,176
Oh no, Jin!

420
00:21:03,176 --> 00:21:06,138
♪

421
00:21:06,138 --> 00:21:08,140
Game over, winner,

422
00:21:08,140 --> 00:21:10,517
Rouga Aragami.

423
00:21:10,517 --> 00:21:13,061
An impact that uses
four gauge to cause

424
00:21:13,061 --> 00:21:15,022
four damage to an opponent?

425
00:21:15,022 --> 00:21:18,025
Even I wasn't expecting
a move like that.

426
00:21:18,025 --> 00:21:21,153
Rouga ends the game with
an impressive impact,

427
00:21:21,153 --> 00:21:23,030
which means Team
Purgatory sweeps

428
00:21:23,030 --> 00:21:25,407
the best‐out‐of‐three match,
making them the first team

429
00:21:25,407 --> 00:21:28,368
to move on to the
finals, booyah!

430
00:21:28,368 --> 00:21:31,872
Everything is going according
to Master Kyoya's plan.

431
00:21:31,872 --> 00:21:34,875
(crowd cheering)

432
00:21:36,919 --> 00:21:38,712
Thanks for the show, Rouga.

433
00:21:38,712 --> 00:21:40,631
Your skills are impressive.

434
00:21:40,631 --> 00:21:44,301
I just hope Gao was
watching, for his sake.

435
00:21:44,301 --> 00:21:45,886
Well played, Jin.

436
00:21:45,886 --> 00:21:47,763
I wish you better
luck next time.

437
00:21:47,763 --> 00:21:51,516
But you know I have to do what's
necessary to win the Gaen Cup,

438
00:21:51,516 --> 00:21:54,478
because I made a sworn
promise to a friend.

439
00:21:54,478 --> 00:21:59,691
♪

440
00:21:59,691 --> 00:22:02,110
Everyone on Team Destiny
has fought against you, Gao,

441
00:22:02,110 --> 00:22:04,821
and it's made them realize
what's important to them.

442
00:22:04,821 --> 00:22:07,824
You shone with the warmth
of the sun on their hearts.

443
00:22:07,824 --> 00:22:11,787
That's why they're doing this,
why they've chosen to help you.

444
00:22:11,787 --> 00:22:14,581
♪

445
00:22:14,581 --> 00:22:17,084
I really need a favor.

446
00:22:17,084 --> 00:22:18,961
Anything for you.

447
00:22:18,961 --> 00:22:20,295
Hear me out.

448
00:22:20,295 --> 00:22:23,131
I want to get my family back,

449
00:22:23,131 --> 00:22:26,593
and I'll need to fight
alongside you to do it.

450
00:22:26,593 --> 00:22:30,764
Are you saying that you actually
wanna become part of my deck?

451
00:22:30,764 --> 00:22:32,766
I am.

452
00:22:32,766 --> 00:22:35,185
♪

453
00:22:35,185 --> 00:22:38,855
Awesome, we're lucky
to have you, my friend.

454
00:22:38,855 --> 00:22:41,817
You won't regret
this, I promise.

455
00:22:41,817 --> 00:22:47,239
♪

456
00:22:49,241 --> 00:22:51,535
‐It's time for‐‐
‐Tasuku and Gao's‐‐

457
00:22:51,535 --> 00:22:53,954
‐Card of the day!
‐Card of the day!

458
00:22:53,954 --> 00:22:56,790
Today we're gonna tell you
about Treachery, Jakikarasu,

459
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:58,792
a new fighting force
for the Skull Warriors.

460
00:22:58,792 --> 00:23:02,087
With 4,000 power, a critical
of 2, and the move ability,

461
00:23:02,087 --> 00:23:05,048
this card's best for equipping
an item or fighting back.

462
00:23:05,048 --> 00:23:06,883
'Cause it's size one,
you can revive it

463
00:23:06,883 --> 00:23:08,301
with Return to the Underworld.

464
00:23:08,301 --> 00:23:10,178
Every Skull Warrior's
deck can use one.

465
00:23:10,178 --> 00:23:13,557
No matter how many times you
defeat it, it keeps coming back!

466
00:23:13,557 --> 00:23:14,891
So what do you think, guys?

467
00:23:14,891 --> 00:23:16,643
You think you can
open up one of these?

468
00:23:16,643 --> 00:23:19,312
You'll never know until you try!

469
00:23:19,312 --> 00:24:45,607
♪

470
00:24:49,569 --> 00:24:52,239
Now that Purgatory Knight's
identity's been revealed,

471
00:24:52,239 --> 00:24:54,407
Gao, Zanya and Baku
find themselves at odds

472
00:24:54,407 --> 00:24:57,410
with each other,
so Tetsuya saves the day!

473
00:24:57,410 --> 00:25:00,705
Next episode, Balle
du Soleil Collapses!

474
00:25:00,705 --> 00:25:03,667
Join us for a Buddyfight!

